Important Points:- 

1.) An ArrayList is resizable array, also called a dynamic array. It grows it size to accomodate new elements
and shrinks the size when the elements are removed

2.) ArrayList internally uses an array to store the elements

3.) ArrayList allows duplicate and null values

4.) ArrayList is an ordered collection, it maintains the order while insertion also.

5.) We cannot create ArrayList like: int,char,boolean 
    We have to create ArrayList like: Integer, Character, Boolean 

6.) Java ArrayList is not synchronized. If multiple threads try to modify an ArrayList at sametime, then final 
    outcome will be non-deterministic. You must explicitly synchronized access to an ArrayList of multiple threads are gonna modify it.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------    

SOME METHODS TO DISCUSS: 

1.) add():- Inserting the new elements to the list
2.) remove():- Removing the new elements to the list
3.) set():- modify the elements at a particular index in ArrayList
4.) get():- access the elements at a particular index in ArrayList
5.) isEmpty():- to check if the list is empty or not
6.) Sorting the List:- 
    a.) Arrays.Sort(arr) ==> Static Sorting
    b.) Collection.Sort(list)  ==> Dynamic Sorting

7.) Traversing:- 

    a.) While loop:- 
        Iterator it = list.iterator()
        while(it.hasNext()){
            SOP(it.next())
        }
    
    b.) For-Each Loop:-
        for(Integer i : list){
            SOP(i);
        }